news.title: UK house prices fall as rising mortgage rates temper property market
news.para: The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (RICS) house price balance, which measures the difference between the percentage of surveyors reporting price rises and those seeing a fall, tumbled to -2 in October from +30 in September.

news.title: After 20 years, Jaipur development body frees own land worth Rs 300 crore from encroachers
news.para: The property was registered in the name of JDA in 1997, and the encroachers had taken possession of it around the same time. The encroachers constructed godowns, warehouses and offices on it.

news.title: WeWork to exit 40 locations in U.S. to cut costs
news.para: The closures, of about 41,000 workstations, are expected to pull down revenue but the simultaneous cost reductions will contribute roughly $140 million to annual adjusted core earnings.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government can't allot house sites to poor in capital region, contend farmers
news.para: The high court held that the lands pooled for one purpose cannot be alienated for other purpose and the notified masterplan cannot be changed.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso tower residents allege lack of clarity over compensation
news.para: Despite this direction, Tower-D allottees said the district administration had muddled the situation. They alleged that the structural audit report on the basis of which the demolition was ordered was not even shared with them.

news.title: Peroorkada flyover construction to hit 95 land owners, 80 commercial firms: SIA report
news.para: As per the report, four houses will be completely demolished for the scheme while nine houses will be partially affected. The land acquisition will also impact 80 commercial buildings.

news.title: Over 600 Chandigarh housing board flats found locked in second survey
news.para: The CHB had decided to carry out a second survey of 1,268 flats allotted under the Rehabilitation Scheme, Small Flat Scheme and the Affordable Rental Housing Scheme which were found locked during the first survey done in July-September.

news.title: Brick makers urge government to bring down GST rate back to 1%
news.para: ​The new GST rate is effective April 1, 2022, Omvir Singh Bhati, General Secretary of the All India Brick and Tile Manufacturers Federation (AIBTMF) told PTI on the sidelines of an event here.

news.title: Chandigarh: Defaulters clear Rs 5.7 lakh property tax dues
news.para: Municipal commissioner Anindita Mitra last week had directed officers to act tough against the property tax defaulters in the city, following the directions, the authorities launched a special sealing drive recently and sealed various properties for not paying their dues for long time.

news.title: Odisha CM to launch drone survey of slums today
news.para: A private agency will conduct the survey to identify genuine beneficiaries of land rights among the slum dwellers. The Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC) had earlier signed an agreement with the agency to conduct the survey.

news.title: Piramal Enterprises logs in Rs 1,536 crore net loss as DHFL merger takes its toll
news.para: Piramal Enterprises said the numbers are not comparable as this is the first time that the company, whose credit business was 90 per cent dominated by wholesale lending earlier, is reporting the earnings as a Reserve Bank-regulated non-banking lender, and also after the merger of DHFL.

news.title: Pune and Pimpri Chinchwad civic bodies seal & attach properties over tax default
news.para: So far, the PMC has sealed 1,355 properties, while the PCMC has attached around 200 properties. The action was taken as the defaulters did not clear the dues despite repeated reminders.

news.title: Prestige Estates' net profit up 54.63% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income from operations stood at Rs 1,474.70 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 9.63 per cent from Rs 1,345.20 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram administration orders evacuation of two towers in Chintels Paradiso
news.para: In March, a preliminary inspection report submitted by IIT-Delhi to a magisterial committee probing the collapse had found that the steel reinforcements in the debris and collapsed portion were corroded and there were rust marks on pieces of concrete.

news.title: Sequoia Capital India sells stake in Indigo Paints for Rs 210 crore
news.para: ​According to the bulk deal data available with the BSE, Sequoia Capital India Investments IV and SCI Investments V sold a total of 15,60,000 shares, amounting to 3.28 per cent stake in the company.
